## M20b(5/5) negative: bare generic type in type position.
##
## `x: Box` (without type arguments) is not a concrete type — only
## `Box(Int)` is. Per GPT-5.5 M20b post-implementation review: the
## type resolver must reject bare references to a generic_type symbol.
##
## EXPECTED: sema error: generic type `Box` requires type arguments.

type Box(T)
  value: T

sub main()
  x: Box = Box(value: 5)
  print(x.value)
